OL,7,FMr Drakeford said while Mr Hart was
OL,8,Fhelpful in areas where he had a role,
OL,9,Ftoo often he was "beginning to get in
OL,10,Fthe way".
OL,12,FHe said: "My difficulty was,
OL,13,Fparticularly in the early days, with
OL,14,Ffrankly, I think, very little else to
OL,15,Fdo, the secretary of state filled his
OL,16,Fdays by writing letters to me asking
OL,17,Fme about the Welsh Government's
OL,18,Fresponsibilities and the risk was that
OL,19,Fhe was beginning to get in the way of
OL,20,Four ability to do the things that we
OL,21,Fneeded to do.
